"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-03-What-makes-your-Olympics-Wang-Guan-s-picks-on-Paris-2024-1vLJsTfomJO-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  Paris hosted the second modern Olympics in 1900, pioneering the inclusion of female athletes. In 1924, Paris introduced the Olympic Village when it hosted the Olympics for the second time, breaking down barriers between athletes from different nations. This tradition of inclusivity continues in 2024, as the ongoing Summer Olympics presents the first mass participation marathon, bridging the gap between elite athletes and the public. There is never been a shortage of laughter, tears, joy or sorrow when it comes to the Olympic Games. What lasting impressions will this year's Games leave on you? Well, here's CGTN's Wang Guan with his personal picks.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"